mplex challenges, from complying with France's secularism laws that strictly prescribe the role of religion in public spaces to preparing for any spillover from two major conflicts raging not far away, the Russia-Ukraine war and the Israel-Hamas war, especially in an era of increased activism by athletes.\", \"from\": 1905, \"to\": 2266, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1998, \"end\": 2004, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9994334845570456, \"rank\": 0.0005619822961818131, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2166, \"end\": 2184, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russo-Ukrainian_War\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Russia-Ukraine war\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russo-Ukrainian_War\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russo-Ukrainian_War\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this year's chaplains\", \"from\": 1909, \"to\": 1930}, {\"ngram\": \"even more complex challenges\", \"from\": 1948, \"to\": 1976}, {\"ngram\": \"the role\", \"from\": 2047, \"to\": 2055}, {\"ngram\": \"religion\", \"from\": 2059, \"to\": 2067}, {\"ngram\": \"public spaces\", \"from\": 2071, \"to\": 2084}, {\"ngram\": \"any spillover\", \"from\": 2102, \"to\": 2115}, {\"ngram\": \"two major conflicts\", \"from\": 2121, \"to\": 2140}, {\"ngram\": \"the Israel-Hamas war\", \"from\": 2189, \"to\": 2209}, {\"ngram\": \"an era\", \"from\": 2225, \"to\": 2231}, {\"ngram\": \"increased activism\", \"from\": 2235, \"to\": 2253}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 2257, \"to\": 2265}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I see our mission as protecting them in their fragility,\\\" said the Rev.\", \"from\": 2268, \"to\": 2340, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our mission\", \"from\": 2275, \"to\": 2286}, {\"ngram\": \"their fragility\", \"from\": 2309, \"to\": 2324}, {\"ngram\": \"the Rev.\", \"from\": 2332, \"to\": 2340}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Anton Gelyasov, archpriest of the Greek-Orthodox Metropolis ofFrance, who's leading more than two dozen Christian Orthodox chaplains for the Games.\", \"from\": 2341, \"to\": 2488, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2375, \"end\": 2389, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_Orthodox_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.195995240457625e-17, \"text\": \"Greek-Orthodox\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_Orthodox_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_Orthodox_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Anton Gelyasov\", \"from\": 2341, \"to\": 2355}, {\"ngram\": \"archpriest\", \"from\": 2357, \"to\": 2367}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 2478, \"to\": 2487}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Second, it's to give witness that we are present, not only as 'my church' but as 'religions,' and that it's good that we are together.\\\"\", \"from\": 2489, \"to\": 2625, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"witness\", \"from\": 2511, \"to\": 2518}, {\"ngram\": \"my church\", \"from\": 2553, \"to\": 2562}, {\"ngram\": \"religions\", \"from\": 2572, \"to\": 2581}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Indeed, the behind-the-scenes dealmaking to accommodate different religions as well as different cultural, national and liturgical traditions within each faith reveals podium-worthy teamwork from the all-volunteer chaplain corps.\", \"from\": 2627, \"to\": 2856, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the-scenes\", \"from\": 2646, \"to\": 2656}, {\"ngram\": \"different religions\", \"from\": 2683, \"to\": 2702}, {\"ngram\": \"different cultural, national and liturgical traditions\", \"from\": 2714, \"to\": 2768}, {\"ngram\": \"each faith\", \"from\": 2776, \"to\": 2786}, {\"ngram\": \"podium-worthy teamwork\", \"from\": 2795, \"to\": 2817}, {\"ngram\": \"the all-volunteer chaplain corps\", \"from\": 2823, \"to\": 2855}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Each religion got 50 square meters (538 square feet) of the tent-like structure that's being constructed and furnished in the village by the Paris Games organizing committee, with a basic mandate to welcome athletes and provide worship information.\", \"from\": 2858, \"to\": 3106, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Each religion\", \"from\": 2858, \"to\": 2871}, {\"ngram\": \"50 square meters\", \"from\": 2876, \"to\": 2892}, {\"ngram\": \"538 square feet\", \"from\": 2894, \"to\": 2909}, {\"ngram\": \"the tent-like structure\", \"from\": 2914, \"to\": 2937}, {\"ngram\": \"the village\", \"from\": 2980, \"to\": 2991}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 2995, \"to\": 3010}, {\"ngram\": \"committee\", \"from\": 3022, \"to\": 3031}, {\"ngram\": \"a basic mandate\", \"from\": 3038, \"to\": 3053}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 3065, \"to\": 3073}, {\"ngram\": \"worship information\", \"from\": 3086, \"to\": 3105}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then, the Jewish and Muslim leaders decided to set up their spaces next to each other, as \\\"an image and example\\\" - in the words of Rabbi Moshe Lewin - that they can coexist even at times of great geopolitical tensions.\", \"from\": 3108, \"to\": 3326, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3118, \"end\": 3124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\", \"score\": 0.999999998630301, \"rank\": 1.36962466001187e-09, \"text\": \"Jewish\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\"}, {\"begin\": 3129, \"end\": 3135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"score\": 0.9948427875538065, \"rank\": 0.005183947162756895, \"text\": \"Muslim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\"}, {\"begin\": 3245, \"end\": 3256, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moshe_Lewin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Moshe Lewin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moshe_Lewin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moshe_Lewin\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their spaces\", \"from\": 3162, \"to\": 3174}, {\"ngram\": \"an image\", \"from\": 3199, \"to\": 3207}, {\"ngram\": \"example\", \"from\": 3212, \"to\": 3219}, {\"ngram\": \"the words\", \"from\": 3226, \"to\": 3235}, {\"ngram\": \"times\", \"from\": 3289, \"to\": 3294}, {\"ngram\": \"great geopolitical tensions\", \"from\": 3298, \"to\": 3325}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Buddhists and Hindus, with the fewest expected adherents, donated half their spaces to theChristians, who will have about 100 chaplains in rotation to serve Catholics, Orthodox and Protestants.\", \"from\": 3328, \"to\": 3521, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3328, \"end\": 3337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Buddhism\", \"score\": 0.9999999999872671, \"rank\": 1.2825252591217056e-11, \"text\": \"Buddhists\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Buddhism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Buddhism\"}, {\"begin\": 3342, \"end\": 3348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hinduism\", \"score\": 0.999998357392072, \"rank\": 1.642610344859397e-06, \"text\": \"Hindus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hinduism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hinduism\"}, {\"begin\": 3485, \"end\": 3494, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.020703551445352e-20, \"text\": \"Catholics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 3496, \"end\": 3504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eastern_Orthodoxy\", \"score\": 0.5669108631107981, \"rank\": 0.7634859947761422, \"text\": \"Orthodox\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eastern_Orthodoxy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eastern_Orthodoxy\"}, {\"begin\": 3509, \"end\": 3520, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/r